The paper focuses on using PageRank algorithm to rank authors in an author co-citation network in the information retrieval (IR) area. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IR (Information Retrieval). The paper also discusses bibliometrics and citation ranking, which could fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of PageRank in evaluating research impact, which could be related to cs.DL (Digital Libraries). The paper also discusses the importance of damping factor in PageRank algorithm, which could be related to cs.SOC (Social and Economic Networks). Finally, the paper proposes weighted PageRank algorithms, which could be related to cs.CYBER (Cybersecurity and Privacy).
